VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \bsplit\s*\(\s*[^;]*\s*\)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:explode|str_split|preg_split && MISSING:test|example
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects usage of the deprecated split() function, which can lead to unpredictable behavior and maintenance challenges.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Deprecated String Split Function.
